<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="D" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Deformed1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Deformed,</orth> adj. 1) misshaped, ill-favoured: Ven. Dedic. <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.767" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 2, 767</bibl> <bibl n="shak. err 4.2.19" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. IV, 2, 19</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 3.3.131" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado III, 3, 131</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 4.2.24" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL IV, 2, 24</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 3.4.402" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. III, 4, 402</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 5.6.51" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C V, 6, 51</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 1.1.20" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 1, 20</bibl>. Superl. <cit><quote>--'st:</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 113.10" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 113, 10</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) apt to deform or disfigure: <cit><quote>careful hours with time's d. hand have written strange defeatures in my face,</quote> <bibl n="shak. err 5.298" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. V, 298</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>